originalText.text: Heather did a home visit with us and our newborn to address some of our breastfeeding concerns. Heather not only educated us and addressed our issues, she also proved to have great bedside manners and she loves kids. Heather is very professional and has good energy, which is critical when you let a stranger into your home.

originalText.text: Heather is an absolute angel.  I highly recommend her! As a new mom, I was surprised at how hard breastfeeding was and there were several issues (supply, latching, our baby's weight, etc.), my husband and I were beside ourselves/stressed and so tired and overwhelmed by it all. Heather made herself available right away and spent over 2 hours with us helping us to resolve every issue! She is patient, professional, warm, and so experienced. Plus, our baby boy loved her and even gave her some smiles at just 4 weeks old! Heather left us with actionable things to do that started to improve everything we were going through as early as that night after she left! She also helped resolve a clogged milk duct. Three weeks later we are doing so well with breastfeeding and we couldn't have made it here without Heather! We are so unbelievably grateful.

originalText.text: Working with Heather recently assured us that our baby was doing fine and gave me the peace of mind that I was producing a lot. After dealing with having to supplement with formula for our 2 week old baby Heather provided with support, empathy and education. Our baby is now 3 months and I've been exclusively breastfeeding since our meeting. Thank you so much!

originalText.text: Heather was a literal godsend. I had to exclusively pump for over a month due to latch issues. Then after working with Heather, my daughter and I were able to transition successfully to breastfeeding. I appreciated her calm demeanor, her strong belief in my daughter and me, and her ongoing help, terrific insights and expertise about breastfeeding, as well as pumping. Breastfeeding was so challenging for us, especially at first, and I would have given up, if it hadn't been for Heather --Josy

originalText.text: Heather is the best! I never write reviews, but needed to take the time to recommend her. She's incredibly warm, knowledgable and professional. To anyone striving for an easier time at breastfeeding- she can help. She was able to come to my apartment during a stressful time and help baby and I establish a painless latch (which I didn't know was possible). Specifically, she accessed baby's anatomy and helped me with specific techniques to improve positioning, my comfort and latch which is now becoming second nature. Highly recommend!
